# Git

## What problem does Git solve?

Allows developers to track changes, collaborate safely, and restore previous versions of a project.

## Key Concepts

- Repository
- Commit
- Branch
- Merge

## Mental Model

Working Directory
↓
Staging Area
↓
Commit
↓
GitHub

## Commands I Used

git status
git add .
git commit -m "..."
git push

## Things I Learned

- Git doesn't track empty folders.
- A commit is a snapshot.
- The staging area lets me choose what goes into the next commit.